** Consultant Construction Programmer wanted **

Would you like to work for one of the most highly regarded international
construction cost, program and advisory consultancies in Brisbane? Providing
valued services to all industry sectors, on some of the most high profile
projects in Brisbane, as well as interstate and overseas, including Queens
Wharf, Waterfront, Brisbane 2032 Olympics Venues, ANU Canberra and Brisbane
Airport?

If you’re seeking a change in direction and looking for a new challenge in
2024, we would love to talk to you.

We are looking for a construction programmer with a minimum 5 years post grad
experience to join our specialist programming, delay claim analysis team based
in our Brisbane office.

Reporting directly to the programming director, this role will provide you
with a unique opportunity to receive valuable mentoring, gain diverse project
experience, as well as expand and develop your knowledge base.

The role of the programmer is to manage all time related aspects of a
construction project, commencing from feasibility and/or design, all the way
through to practical completion.

If you are an enthusiastic, ambitious team player with an ability to think
logically and strategically with excellent communication skills, then this
could be the role you have been looking for.

** Position requirements include: **

• Australian Citizen or Permanent resident

• Degree or higher qualification in Construction Management is preferred

• Experience using Primavera P6, Microsoft Project or Powerproject

• Experience using Microsoft Office applications including Word and Excel

• Previous Australian construction industry experience would be an advantage

• Ability to communicate effectively (written and oral)

• Ability to prioritise and multi task effectively

• Ability to work well as part of a team

• Full Australian driving licence

